The paper deals with the problem of drawing non-crossing paths in a geographic network, which is a graph whose vertices are restricted to a prescribed region in the plane. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which suggests that it could be categorized under algorithms and complexity (cs.DM), as well as game theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
